HEADWORD: Corvee
<hw>Cor`vee"</hw> <pr>(k?r`v" ⟦or⟧ -v?")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>corv⟦eacute⟧e</ets>, fr. LL. <ets>corvada</ets>,
<ets>corrogata</ets>, fr. L. <ets>corrogare</ets> to entreat together;
<ets>cor-</ets> + <ets>rogare</ets> to ask.]</ety> <fld>(Feudal
Law)</fld> <def>An obligation to perform certain services, as the repair
of roads, for the lord or sovereign.</def>⟦br⟧
